  • public class CampusETA
extends Campus
    The CampusETA Class inherits from Campus Class, which handle the actual calculation of distance between the 2 locations indicated by user and store the time required as instance variable.

      • locationValid

        public static boolean locationValid(java.lang.String startPoint,
                                    java.lang.String endPoint)
                             throws java.net.MalformedURLException,
                                    java.io.IOException
        This method will check if the location / room inputted by user is valid before calculating the actual estimated time for the user to walk between. It is supposed to be called in Category class.
        Parameters:
        startPoint - First parameter taken by the method, representing the current position of the user.
        endPoint - Second parameter taken by the method, representing the destination of user.
        Returns:
        Boolean This method will return a boolean value indicating whether the 2 locations inputted by the user is correct. True when valid locations, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        java.net.MalformedURLException
        java.io.IOException
